  "response": "Rust on a 2012 Nissan engine depends on the location and extent of the rust:\n\n1. Surface rust:\n- Normal and usually not a major concern\n- Typically cosmetic\n- Can be cleaned and treated\n\n2. Significant rust:\n- Could indicate potential structural or component damage\n- May affect engine performance\n- Might signal coolant or oil leaks\n- Could compromise engine integrity\n\nRecommended steps:\n- Inspect the rust carefully\n- Determine the rust's location and depth\n- Have a mechanic evaluate if it's serious\n- Check for underlying issues causing rust\n- Consider professional treatment or repair\n\nFactors affecting rust:\n- Climate\n- Regular maintenance\n- Exposure to road salt\n- Storage conditions\n\nIf the rust is extensive or you're unsure, it's best to have a professional mechanic inspect the engine to assess potential risks and necessary repairs.",
